{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_31","type":"command_execution","command":"\"C:\\\\WINDOWS\\\\System32\\\\WindowsPowerShell\\\\v1.0\\\\powershell.exe\" -Command '$p='\"'production_mirror\\\\nodes\\\\_otr_story_brief_helpers.py'; \"'$i=1; Get-Content -LiteralPath $p | ForEach-Object { if(($i -ge 228 -and $i -le 255) -or ($i -ge 450 -and $i -le 570)){ '\"'{0}:{1}' -f \"'$i, $_ }; $i++ }'","aggregated_output":"228:#: _DEFAULT_ERA_TAIL, otr_video_plan.py).\r\n229:ERA_TAIL_DEFAULT = \"timeless cinematic aesthetic\"\r\n230:\r\n231:#: The film aesthetic tail (legacy _DEFAULT_STYLE_TAIL, otr_video_plan.py).\r\n232:STYLE_TAIL_DEFAULT = (\"cinematic, 35mm film look, subtle film grain, \"\r\n233:                      \"volumetric lighting\")\r\n234:\r\n235:#: BUG-411 restore (2026-06-14): the 6/5 FLUX image pipeline\r\n236:#: (visual/batch_flux_render.py) appended a RICHER cinematic grade than the\r\n237:#: shared STYLE_TAIL_DEFAULT. The image-pipeline rewrite into\r\n238:#: _otr_image_engines dropped the \"anamorphic lens, heavy vignette, muted color\r\n239:#: grade, sharp focus\" grade descriptors (legacy _DEFAULT_STYLE_SUFFIX), which\r\n240:#: flattened the look. Re-added on the IMAGE STILL path ONLY\r\n241:#: (compose_still_prompt, after STYLE_TAIL_DEFAULT); the shared tail that LTX\r\n242:#: scene clips + character video (style_tail=True) use stays untouched.\r\n243:IMAGE_GRADE_TAIL = (\"anamorphic lens, heavy vignette, muted color grade, \"\r\n244:                    \"sharp focus\")\r\n245:\r\n246:#: BUG-411: the 6/5 radio bookend / radio stills carried a broadcast-distress\r\n247:#: identity suffix appended to every radio prompt (legacy _RADIO_PROMPT_SUFFIX);\r\n248:#: the \"35mm film grain, broadcast-distressed\" grade IS the lush distressed\r\n249:#: tint the operator wants back. Re-added to the radio scene stills\r\n250:#: (open/announcer/music) so they read as a distressed period broadcast still.\r\n251:RADIO_BROADCAST_TAIL = (\"35mm film grain, broadcast-distressed cinematic \"\r\n252:                        \"aesthetic, centered composition\")\r\n253:\r\n254:#: The render-constraint clause the LTX scene prompts carry; preserved\r\n255:#: verbatim through max_chars trimming.\r\n450:STILL_FRAMING_SCENE_CHARACTER = (\r\n451:    \"cinematic medium shot, the character framed within a wide 16:9 environment, \"\r\n452:    \"full head and shoulders with clear headroom inside frame, face unobstructed, \"\r\n453:    \"balanced landscape composition\")\r\n454:\r\n455:\r\n456:def compose_still_prompt(meta: Any, *, kind: str, role: str = \"\",\r\n457:                         beat_id: str = \"\", char_entry: Any = None) -> str:\r\n458:    \"\"\"ONE still-image prompt in the legacy 5-layer order: subject /\r\n459:    setting top-2 / framing hint / TRIMMED era tail (still profile) /\r\n460:    style tail. Scene kinds append the :data:`NO_TEXT_CLAUSE` (a render\r\n461:    constraint stills must carry; portraits never need it).\r\n462:\r\n463:    ``kind``: ``\"portrait\"`` leads with the character's own description\r\n464:    (``portrait_prompt`` -> ``appearance`` -> ``character_description`` on\r\n465:    ``char_entry``); ``\"scene_character\"`` (BUG 1, 2026-06-20) ALSO leads with\r\n466:    the character description but composes a WIDE 16:9 medium shot (the landscape\r\n467:    still-only character beat -- still_flat/still_pan/ltx_video) and DROPS the\r\n468:    radio-booth tail; every other scene kind (``scene_open`` / ``scene_beat``)\r\n469:    leads with :func:`get_open_subject` (``synthetic`` = kind==\"scene_open\"\r\n470:    -- the b000 opening-music beat is the synthetic open). Pure; never\r\n471:    raises; never returns empty (the subject layer always exists).\r\n472:    \"\"\"\r\n473:    is_portrait = (kind == \"portrait\")\r\n474:    is_char_scene = (kind == \"scene_character\")\r\n475:    if is_portrait or is_char_scene:\r\n476:        # Both lead with the CHARACTER's own description; scene_character just\r\n477:        # frames them in a wide environment instead of a tight portrait.\r\n478:        ce = char_entry if isinstance(char_entry, dict) else {}\r\n479:        subject = str(ce.get(\"portrait_prompt\") or ce.get(\"appearance\")\r\n480:                      or ce.get(\"character_description\") or \"\").strip()\r\n481:        if not subject:\r\n482:            subject = \"a period-dressed character, face clearly visible\"\r\n483:    else:\r\n484:        subject = get_open_subject(role, synthetic=(kind == \"scene_open\"), meta=meta)\r\n485:    m = _meta(meta)\r\n486:    terms = m.get(\"story_brief_terms\") or {}\r\n487:    if not isinstance(terms, dict):\r\n488:        terms = {}\r\n489:    setting = \", \".join([str(t).strip() for t in (terms.get(\"setting\") or [])\r\n490:                         if str(t).strip()][:2])\r\n491:    if is_portrait:\r\n492:        framing = STILL_FRAMING_PORTRAIT\r\n493:    elif is_char_scene:\r\n494:        framing = STILL_FRAMING_SCENE_CHARACTER\r\n495:    elif kind == \"scene_beat\":\r\n496:        framing = STILL_FRAMING_SCENE_BEAT\r\n497:    else:\r\n498:        framing = STILL_FRAMING_OPEN\r\n499:    pieces = [subject]\r\n500:    if setting:\r\n501:        pieces.append(setting)\r\n502:    pieces.append(framing)\r\n503:    pieces.append(get_era_tail(meta, profile=\"still\"))\r\n504:    pieces.append(STYLE_TAIL_DEFAULT)\r\n505:    if not is_portrait:\r\n506:        # BUG-411: restore the 6/5 cinematic grade + the radio broadcast-distress\r\n507:        # identity the image-pipeline rewrite dropped. Scene stills are all radio\r\n508:        # context (open/announcer/music), so both tails apply; appended AFTER the\r\n509:        # shared STYLE_TAIL_DEFAULT and BEFORE the NO_TEXT_CLAUSE so the 5-layer\r\n510:        # order and the no-text contract are preserved. Portraits are unchanged\r\n511:        # (they keep their three-quarter framing + the shared style tail).\r\n512:        pieces.append(IMAGE_GRADE_TAIL)\r\n513:        # BUG 1 (2026-06-20): the character SCENE still is NOT a radio booth --\r\n514:        # it shows the character in their world, so the broadcast-booth tail\r\n515:        # (\"centered composition\", broadcast-distress) is dropped for this kind.\r\n516:        if not is_char_scene:\r\n517:            pieces.append(RADIO_BROADCAST_TAIL)\r\n518:    out = \", \".join(p.strip().rstrip(\",\") for p in pieces if p and p.strip())\r\n519:    if not is_portrait:\r\n520:        out = f\"{out}, {NO_TEXT_CLAUSE}\"\r\n521:    return out\r\n522:\r\n523:\r\n524:def finish_visual_prompt(meta: Any, prompt: str, *, max_chars: int = 0,\r\n525:                         style_tail: bool = True,\r\n526:                         era_profile: str = \"full\") -> str:\r\n527:    \"\"\"``prompt + \", \" + era_tail [+ \", \" + STYLE_TAIL_DEFAULT]`` -- the one\r\n528:    shared finishing seam every visual prompt site calls.\r\n529:\r\n530:    ``max_chars`` (0 = uncapped): word-boundary trim of the FINISHED string\r\n531:    for budgeted consumers (LTX motion budget is 220-240 chars); a trailing\r\n532:    :data:`NO_TEXT_CLAUSE` present in ``prompt`` survives the trim (it is a\r\n533:    render constraint, not flavor). Callers run their guards BEFORE this and\r\n534:    compute prompt hashes AFTER it. Pure; never raises; empty ``prompt``\r\n535:    returns '' (finishing never invents a subject).\r\n536:\r\n537:    ``era_profile`` (LTX-I2V ticket Part A, 2026-06-11): passed through to\r\n538:    :func:`get_era_tail`. Default ``\"full\"`` = every pre-existing call site,\r\n539:    byte-identical. The LTX scene composer passes ``\"still\"`` so VIDEO\r\n540:    prompts share the stills' trimmed palette diet (the full top-3 palette\r\n541:    tail is what dragged LTX scene clips reddish while the FLUX stills,\r\n542:    already on the still profile, stayed balanced).\r\n543:    \"\"\"\r\n544:    base = (prompt or \"\").strip().rstrip(\",\")\r\n545:    if not base:\r\n546:        return \"\"\r\n547:    # Preserve the clause only when TRAILING (pass-02 panel: an occurrence\r\n548:    # mid-prompt is content, not a render constraint to relocate).\r\n549:    keep_no_text = base.endswith(NO_TEXT_CLAUSE)\r\n550:    if keep_no_text:\r\n551:        base = base[: -len(NO_TEXT_CLAUSE)].strip().rstrip(\",\").strip()\r\n552:    pieces = [base, get_era_tail(meta, profile=era_profile)]\r\n553:    if style_tail:\r\n554:        pieces.append(STYLE_TAIL_DEFAULT)\r\n555:    out = \", \".join(p for p in pieces if p)\r\n556:    if max_chars and len(out) > max_chars:\r\n557:        budget = max_chars - (len(NO_TEXT_CLAUSE) + 2 if keep_no_text else 0)\r\n558:        cut = out[:max(budget, 20)]\r\n559:        idx = cut.rfind(\" \")\r\n560:        if idx >= 20:\r\n561:            cut = cut[:idx]\r\n562:        out = cut.rstrip(\" ,\")\r\n563:    if keep_no_text:\r\n564:        out = f\"{out}, {NO_TEXT_CLAUSE}\"\r\n565:    if max_chars and len(out) > max_chars:\r\n566:        # Hard guarantee for pathological small caps (pass-02 panel): the\r\n567:        # cap wins even over the preserved clause + the 20-char floor.\r\n568:        out = out[:max_chars].rstrip(\" ,\")\r\n569:    return out\r\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
