{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_43","type":"agent_message","text":"VERDICT: no. The plan still has undefined schemas, an invalid template-variable rule, and unresolved production interface collisions that will stop implementation or produce wrong bridge data.\n\nMUST-FIX BEFORE BUILD:\n1. [Seams: templates vs generated fields vs bindings] Template validation rule is not implementable as written. “label-substitution only, variable allowlist derived from the resolved profile model fields” conflicts with real production templates that require runtime variables: `_INVENTOR_USER_TEMPLATE` uses `{n_required}`, `{seed_sample_block}`, `{article_excerpt}` and `_CHOOSER_USER_TEMPLATE` uses `{article_excerpt}`, `{candidates_block}` in `production_mirror/nodes/_otr_style_picker.py:301` and `production_mirror/nodes/_otr_style_picker.py:334`. Concrete fix: define a per-seam variable allowlist with both profile labels and runtime variables, e.g. `style_pick_inventor={n_required, seed_sample_block, article_excerpt}` and `style_pick_chooser={article_excerpt, candidates_block}`; do not derive it only from `StoryPromptProfile` fields.\n\n2. [Tonight's build C1/C2] `SourceBankSpec`, `PipelineSpec`, `BridgeArtifact`, `FetchRequest`, and `LlmFns` are named but not specified. The current workspace has no `src/upstream_story_lab/` or `fixtures/`, and the recovered snapshot at `41c6512` has `src/upstream_story_lab/contracts.py` but no `fixtures/banks.json` or `fixtures/pipelines.json` to recover. Concrete fix: add exact Pydantic field lists and minimal JSON examples for `banks.json`, `pipelines.json`, and `BridgeArtifact` before coding; treat banks/pipelines as new work, not recovered assets.\n\n3. [Compatibility mirrors / C1] “three-mirror emit” is ambiguous and conflicts with production’s data locations. `meta.news` is `NewsBriefs.model_dump()` in `production_mirror/nodes/OTR_LedgerScriptWriter.py:2887`; `news_article` is an internal resolved dict at `production_mirror/nodes/OTR_LedgerScriptWriter.py:1376`; `news_used` is a JSON output socket built by `_build_news_payload()` at `production_mirror/nodes/OTR_LedgerScriptWriter.py:1500`. Concrete fix: define bridge output keys explicitly: `meta_mirrors.news`, `meta_mirrors.news_seed`, and optionally `news_used_payload`; do not call internal `news_article` a meta mirror unless an adapter consumes it.\n\n4. [Generated Content Fields / Compatibility mirrors] Field naming is inconsistent. The plan’s generated field is `close_brief`, but production `NewsBriefs` field is `news_close_brief` at `production_mirror/nodes/news_interpreter.py:155` and `production_mirror/nodes/news_interpreter.py:167`. Concrete fix: keep `StoryInputPacket.close_brief` only if `bridge.py` explicitly maps it to `meta.news.news_close_brief`; add a test that `meta.news` keys exactly match the 13 `NewsBriefs` fields and that `key_terms` is a list per `production_mirror/nodes/_otr_ledger_freeze.py:232`.\n\n5. [Locked vocabulary / C5] New `visual_style` collides with production’s existing `style` / `style_custom` widget semantics. The writer already resolves `style` as a tonal descriptor at `production_mirror/nodes/OTR_LedgerScriptWriter.py:1220` and documents it as “Tonal preset for the outline” at `production_mirror/nodes/OTR_LedgerScriptWriter.py:1871`. Append-only widgets mean those old inputs remain. Concrete fix: specify whether old `style` becomes legacy story-tone, is ignored when `story_model` is set, or is bridged into `story_model`; define exact `run()` defaults and precedence for `source_bank`, `story_model`, `story_pipeline`, `visual_style`, `style`, and `style_custom`.\n\n6. [Fallback taxonomy] The fallback inventory is incomplete. It names style-picker candidate padding, title regen, and announcer outro fallback, but production also has chooser fallback to first candidate at `production_mirror/nodes/_otr_style_picker.py:768`, RSS style slug substitution to `mission_control_procedural` at `production_mirror/nodes/OTR_LedgerScriptWriter.py:1142`, and raw-news degradation when `news_briefs_required=False` around `production_mirror/nodes/OTR_LedgerScriptWriter.py:2857`. Concrete fix: add each site to `FALLBACK_INVENTORY` with a per-lane decision and tests proving non-science lanes cannot reach them.\n\nSHOULD-FIX:\n1. [C5 production-SHAPED modules tested in lab] “tested in lab” is too broad against a dependency-incomplete mirror. `production_mirror/nodes/OTR_LedgerScriptWriter.py:131` imports `._otr_story_brief`, and `production_mirror/nodes/_otr_outline.py:37` imports `._otr_episode_budget`; those files are not in `PRODUCTION_MIRROR_MANIFEST.md`. Fix: either expand the mirror or state C5 tests are AST/syntax/pure-module tests only.\n\n2. [C3 AST drift] Required-subset matching for `meta.news_seed` is too weak if the bridge emits a complete mirror. The adapter only reads `headline` and `source` at `production_mirror/nodes/_otr_legacy_to_stage1_adapter.py:95`, but the documented current shape includes `url`, `date`, `body_chars`, `style`, `selected_at` at `production_mirror/nodes/_otr_legacy_to_stage1_adapter.py:71`. Fix: required-subset is fine for consumer drift, but bridge-shape tests should require all emitted keys and types.\n\n3. [C1 / dependencies] The current tree has no `requirements.txt`; the recovered `41c6512:requirements.txt` pins `pydantic>=2.0,<3.0`. Fix: restore or recreate dependency metadata before adding Pydantic v2 models.\n\n4. [C2 PD packet shape] PD path safety says `source_text_ref + manifest with text_files/image_files` and `rights_status=public_domain enforced`, but symlink behavior and base-directory resolution are unspecified. Fix: require `Path.resolve()` containment under the manifest folder and reject symlinks escaping that root.\n\nOPTIONAL / NICE-TO-HAVE:\n- Add a small “bridge artifact example” JSON in the plan. It would collapse several ambiguous interfaces into one testable target.\n\nCUT THESE (over-engineering):\n1. [C3] Full canonical hash